cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper is about Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs), which are a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also covers the backpropagation algorithm, which is a widely used optimization algorithm in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. ANNs are often used in computer vision applications, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, ANNs can be used in control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
